  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, an act that requires a penalty to provide specific and general deterrence. However, there are significant mitigating factors present in this case: the defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of behavior, and they have already partially repaid the stolen funds, demonstrating taking some responsibility and a willingness to make the victim whole. Balancing the severity of the white-collar offense with these mitigating circumstances, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to emphasize the seriousness of the crime, followed by a mandate to complete full restitution.",
